article.headline: Jacksonville St. 80, Norfolk St. 61
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- Nick Murphy scored 18 points off the bench and Geddes Robinson added 17 as Jacksonville State defeated Norfolk State 80-61 Tuesday night. The Gamecocks (5-1) shot 78.3 percent from the field (18 of 23) in the second half, finishing at 58.5 percent (31 of 53). Leading 35-29 at halftime, Jacksonville State built a 44-31 lead with 15:46 left. The Spartans (1-4) cut the lead to four on Brandon Monroe's dunk with 8:36 left, but the Gamecocks scored the next six points to pull away. Michael Deloach scored a game-high 25 points for the Spartans, who have lost four straight. Brandon Crawford added 13 points for the Gamecocks. Neither team led by more than six points in a first half as they combined for 27 fouls. Norfolk State led 24-20 with 6:57 left in the opening half, but the Gamecocks went on an 8-0 run to take the lead for good.
